				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				When my friend a venerable lvl 53 SK told me to read the posting that a GROUP gets penalized for including us hybrids....and i should go read postings....i have ended up in web-land.  I am not, as so many of my fellow players, a SYS ADMIN or a programmer.....i am the EQ equivalent of what a talented woodpusher would be in chess.  I play by the seat of my pants....and only occasionally consult the internet....because....i rely on the kindness of my friends to point me in the directions of essentials.  Now i have read it.  I CANT BELIEVE VERANT IS SO BLANTANTLY UNCONCERNED ABOUT THE UNFAIRNESS TO THOSE OF US WHO PLAY HYBRIDS.  This 40% exp penalty on groups that include us....is not there in the introductory book which most of us duffers use when forming our first characters to whom we are very attached.<BR>
<BR>
I think I speak for many hybrid players when I say, go ahead and be unfair and penalize US if you think somehow you can find a reasonable logic to do so....but to penalize GROUPS that include us is basically to create a caste of EQ untouchables....and it also means pretty much that if TWO hybrids are in one group....the exp goes down the drain.  My friend was angry and thinking of quitting EQ because of this and similar Verant-created and BLIGHTLY UNREPAIRED inequities.  I am very angry like him, but in my case it just drops my RESPECT a few notches all over again!<BR>
<BR>
(The game does not advertise itself as a game where one is REQUIRED to pass several graduate level programming classes in order to really understand what is going on.....I'm shocked that Verant is allowing it to increasingly drift in this direction.)
