				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Rennis, I had to add this.<BR>
<BR>
You think groups with hybrids gain exp slower?  You must be camping orcs in EC or some other &quot;sit and wait&quot; spawn.  A group mix (20+) of enchanter, cleric, necro, ranger, rogue, paladin will gain MORE exp than the same minus hybrids replaced with warriors.  You think because the hybrids will suck more exp from kills that that makes the group earn more.  Per kill yes, but this group has next to nil downtime, where one with warriors attacking the same mobs WILL have downtime.  You think like a bean counter, and that might have worked in school and math class, but not in this case.  There is an exp penalty for a reason.  Groups with hybrids have less downtime and kill more faster than groups with all &quot;pets&quot;.
